National Semiconductor Corpsaid improved results at its Semiconductor Group helped reducelosses in the third quarter and nine months.    In the quarter ended March 8, the group had a modest salesincrease and major improvement in operating performancecompared to the year-ago quarter, the company said.    But results softened from the prior quarter because of lowbookings last fall for third quarter shipment and holidayshutdowns, it said.    The semiconductor maker cut net losses to 25.6 mln dlrs or31 cts a share from 39.4 mln dlrs or 47 cts in the quarter.    Losses in the nine months were reduced to 32.7 mln dlrs or44 cts from 84.4 mln dlrs or one dlr. Sales grew 23.5 pct inthe quarter to 398.1 mln dlrs and 25.5 pct in the nine monthsto 1.36 billion dlrs.    Bookings recovered in the latter part of the third quarter,the company said. Despite the improvement in order rates andoperating results year-to-year, pricing continues to be"aggressive for many products," it said.    Nevertheless, it expects the semiconductor business willcontinue to improve this year. The Information Systems Groupwill continue strong sales growth based on recent order trendsand new product introductions, it said. Reuter&#3;